The paper proposes a new algorithm for K-means clustering that is more efficient than the classical Lloyd-Max algorithm. The algorithm is based on compressive sensing techniques and is demonstrated to perform well on large datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the algorithm, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper presents results on handwritten digits classification, which indicates a possible connection with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
